FBIS4-13980 "drnes080_s_94017" FBIS-NES-94-080 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 Iran Women Allowed To Be Advisers at Courts Women Allowed To Be Advisers at Courts LD2404104694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 24 Apr 94 LD2404104694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Excerpt] In today's open session of the Islamic Consultative Majles, the bill on reforming the conditions of choosing judges of the Ministry of Justice was approved. According to our correspondent, the bill provides for women who are eligible for appointment as judges of the Ministry of Justice and who have a judicial background to be employed as advisers at the administrative court of justice, the special civil courts, the public prosecutor's office, the investigations department, the office of legal studies, the legislative office of the Ministry of Justice [as heard], the office for the supervision of minors, the legal office, and other offices with judicial positions. [passage omitted]
